node.title: Victoria records 1,273 new COVID-19 cases and eight deaths
node.alt: A busy shopping mall with multiple pedestrians in Melbourne's CBD.
node.description: There are now 13,813 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 453 people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,273\u00a0new COVID-19 cases and eight\u00a0deaths as the state enters a new phase of the pandemic with fewer restrictions.", "There are now 13,813\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 453\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.", "There are 330\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 57\u00a0are in intensive care and 30\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 58\u00a0people were in intensive care but their COVID-19 infections were no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 73,020\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 5,842\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, and more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "Victoria has now fully vaccinated more than 88\u00a0per cent of its\u00a0population aged 12 and up.", "More to come.", "", "
COVID cases surging across several European countries
"]
